  "body": "I'm trying to run `hardhat` on FreeBSD, for which there isn't an official `solc` binary.\r\nWhen I run `npx hardhat compile` it correctly download the solcjs file into `$HOME/.cache/hardhat-nodejs/compilers/wasm/soljson-v0.8.4+commit.c7e474f2.js`, but it tries to run it as a native binary instead of using the javascript wrapper, failing miserably with the following error:\r\n```\r\nError: write EPIPE\r\n    at afterWriteDispatched (internal/stream_base_commons.js:156:25)\r\n    at writeGeneric (internal/stream_base_commons.js:147:3)\r\n    at Socket._writeGeneric (net.js:798:11)\r\n    at Socket._write (net.js:810:8)\r\n    at writeOrBuffer (internal/streams/writable.js:358:12)\r\n    at Socket.Writable.write (internal/streams/writable.js:303:10)\r\n    at output (node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/solidity/compiler/index.ts:73:22)\r\n    at new Promise (<anonymous>)\r\n    at NativeCompiler.compile (node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/solidity/compiler/index.ts:59:34)\r\n    at SimpleTaskDefinition.action (node_modules/hardhat/src/builtin-tasks/compile.ts:665:37)\r\n```\r\n",
